      "role": "user",
      "content": "Interesting. So you're saying the \"doomer\" arguments are basically just alarmism. But if even a small group of highly respected researchers—like Geoffrey Hinton or Yoshua Bengio—are sounding the alarm about catastrophic risks, isn't it a bit dismissive to call it a myth? Doesn't that imply that we should at least be taking some precautionary measures just in case, rather than just assuming they're wrong?",
